      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:61:5",
      "text": [
        " رَجُلٍ رَجَعَ عَنِ الْإِسْلَامِ قَالَ يُسْتَتَابُ فَإِنْ تَابَ وَ إِلَّا قُتِلَ "
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Isa, from Ali Bin Hadeed, from Jameel Bin Darraj, and others, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from one of the two (5<sup>th</sup> or 6<sup>th</sup> Imam<sup>asws</sup>) regarding a man who retracted from Al-Islam. He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘He would be told to repent, so if he does repent (fine), or else killed’."
        ]
      }
